-- "run drops stdout on panic" regression — a RAW `panic "…"` call site in
-- eval.mdk that does NOT go through runtimePanic (here: `lookupFrames [] name
-- = panic (...)`, hit because the interpreter has no dispatch-table entry for
-- `flushStdout`).  Representative of the ~20 similar internal-invariant call
-- sites (evalIndex/evalSlice/evalRange/applyClosure/collectPartials/pPutStr/…)
-- that fire when the interpreter meets a value shape it doesn't expect ("type
-- confusion" class) -- they all compile to the SAME native `panic` extern
-- call our fix covers, so this one call site stands in for the whole class.
-- See index_oob.mdk for the full writeup.
--
-- Was `exit 3` until eval.mdk grew a real `exit` binding (2026-07-14,
-- ioExternBindings) — `exit` no longer reaches this raw-panic path under
-- `run` (it now cleanly exits 3, see test/CAPABILITY-EXCEPTIONS.txt's
-- promoted `exit` row), so this fixture switched to `flushStdout`, one of
-- the remaining interp-BUG externs (unbound under `run`, bound under
-- `build`) that still exercises the same "unbound identifier" raw-panic
-- call site. run-only for the same reason `exit` was: `medaka build`
-- implements `flushStdout` (isIoExtern) so it does not panic there.
main : <IO, Stdout> Unit
main =
  println "SENTINEL"
  flushStdout ()
